Liability Disclaimer:
This software controls Tesla Powerwall backup reserve settings. Users are
responsible for:
- Ensuring compliance with local utility requirements
- Understanding the impact of backup reserve changes on home energy systems
- Monitoring the system for proper operation
- Having backup plans for power outages

The authors and contributors provide this software "as is" and assume no
responsibility for any damages, power outages, or energy system issues that
may result from its use.

Security Notice:
This software handles Tesla API credentials and AWS credentials. Users are
responsible for:
- Keeping all credentials secure and private
- Following security best practices
- Regularly rotating credentials
- Monitoring for unauthorized access

Support Notice:
This is open-source software provided by the community. While we strive to
provide helpful documentation and support, users should expect to:
- Follow documentation carefully
- Troubleshoot issues independently
- Contribute back to the project when possible
- Respect maintainer time and resources

Data Privacy:
This software may process energy usage data and personal information. Users
should:
- Understand what data is being accessed and transmitted
- Ensure compliance with local privacy laws
- Secure their notification channels (Discord, email, etc.)
- Regularly review access permissions

Commercial Use:
While this software is provided under the MIT license allowing commercial use,
users engaging in commercial activities should:
